{"title":"Retail banking market investigation: infographics","public_updated_at":"2016-08-09T06:00:00Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>In August 2016, the Competition and Markets Authority (<abbr title=\"Competition and Markets Authority\">CMA</abbr>) published its <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/cma-cases/review-of-banking-for-small-and-medium-sized-businesses-smes-in-the-uk\">final report</a> following its investigation into the retail banking market.</p>\n\n<p>We found that older and larger banks do not have to work hard enough to win and retain customers, so it’s difficult for new and smaller banks to grow. Our proposals include changes to help consumers and microbusinesses find a better deal and the quicker adoption of open banking.</p>\n\n<p>The infographics illustrate how open banking works and the timetable for the implementation of remedies to reform the personal and business current account markets.</p>\n\n<p>We’ve also published a <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/retail-banking-market-investigation-overview\">short overview</a> of our investigation and some other <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/cma-gov-uk/\">visuals</a>.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2016-08-09T07:00:00.000+01:00","note":"First published."}],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1672367\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544943/what-is-open-banking.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544943/thumbnail_what-is-open-banking.pdf.png\" /></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"attachment-details\">\n    <h2 class=\"title\"><a href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544943/what-is-open-banking.pdf\">What is open banking?</a></h2>\n    <p class=\"metadata\">\n        <span class=\"type\"><abbr title=\"Portable 